    stem: "A 35-year-old woman who is 28 weeks pregnant presents with increasing dyspnoea on minimal exertion. She emigrated from India 5 years ago. On examination, there is a low-pitched mid-diastolic murmur at the apex with a loud S1 and an opening snap. HR is 95 bpm in atrial fibrillation. Echocardiography confirms severe mitral stenosis with MVA of 0.9 cm² and mean gradient of 14 mmHg, with no significant subvalvular disease. What is the most appropriate management?",
