    stem: "A 65-year-old man with ischaemic cardiomyopathy (ejection fraction 28%) is found on Holter monitor to have runs of non-sustained ventricular tachycardia (NSVT). He is currently on optimal medical therapy including carvedilol, ramipril, spironolactone, and eplerenone. He has no prior history of sustained VT or cardiac arrest. An electrophysiology (EP) study demonstrates inducible sustained VT. What is the most appropriate next management step?",
