    stem: "A 68-year-old man with a 40 pack-year smoking history attends his GP for a health check. He is asymptomatic. He has never had a vascular imaging study. His GP orders an abdominal aortic ultrasound as part of the National Vascular Disease Prevention Alliance screening program. The ultrasound reveals an infrarenal abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) measuring 3.8 cm in maximum diameter. His BP is 138/86 mmHg and he takes amlodipine. What is the most appropriate management?",
