    stem: "A 32-year-old male competitive cyclist collapses during a race and is resuscitated from ventricular fibrillation. He has a family history of a brother who died suddenly at age 28. On examination he has a prominent left ventricular apex and a loud ejection systolic murmur at the left sternal border that increases in intensity with Valsalva manoeuvre and decreases with squatting. Echocardiography reveals asymmetric septal hypertrophy with a septal thickness of 22 mm and systolic anterior motion of the mitral valve. What is the most appropriate long-term management to prevent sudden cardiac death?",
