    stem: "A 67-year-old male smoker with hypertension presents to the ED with sudden onset of severe tearing chest pain radiating to his back. His BP is 180/100 mmHg in the right arm and 145/88 mmHg in the left arm. He is diaphoretic and appears in severe distress. A chest X-ray shows a widened mediastinum. His ECG shows no ischaemic changes. What is the most appropriate immediate investigation to confirm the diagnosis?",
