    topic: "Cardiovascular",
    subtopic: "Heart Failure",
    stem: "A 74-year-old man is admitted with acute decompensated heart failure. He has bilateral pulmonary oedema on CXR, an SpO2 of 89% on room air, and is in significant respiratory distress. His BP is 160/95 mmHg and HR is 100 bpm. He has known HFrEF (EF 35%) and is on optimal medical therapy. His creatinine is 130 µmol/L. Which of the following interventions has the strongest evidence for reducing intubation rates and improving short-term outcomes in this situation?",
