    stem: "A 34-year-old woman who is 28 weeks pregnant presents with progressive dyspnoea, orthopnoea, and a 3-week history of haemoptysis. On auscultation there is a loud S1, an opening snap, and a low-pitched mid-diastolic rumble at the cardiac apex. BP is 110/70 mmHg and HR is 108 bpm. Echocardiography shows a mitral valve area of 1.2 cm² with a mean gradient of 9 mmHg. Left atrial dilatation is present. What is the most appropriate management?",
