    stem: "A 65-year-old woman with known ischaemic cardiomyopathy presents with worsening dyspnoea over 3 weeks, orthopnoea, and bilateral ankle oedema. Her medications include metoprolol succinate 50 mg daily and perindopril 5 mg daily. On examination, JVP is elevated at 6 cm above the sternal angle, bibasal crackles are present, and she has 2+ pitting oedema to the knees. Her echocardiogram shows LVEF of 32%. What is the most appropriate addition to her current medication regimen?",
