    id: "cv-b8-018",
    topic: "Cardiovascular",
    subtopic: "Cardiomyopathy",
    stem: "A 38-year-old woman presents with progressive dyspnoea and ankle oedema that started 6 weeks after delivering her first child. She is currently breastfeeding. Echocardiogram shows a dilated left ventricle with LVEF of 28% and no regional wall motion abnormalities. Coronary angiography is normal. She is haemodynamically stable. What is the most appropriate pharmacological management?",
