    subtopic: "STEMI/NSTEMI",
    stem: "A 58-year-old male smoker presents to the emergency department with a 45-minute history of severe central crushing chest pain radiating to his left arm, associated with diaphoresis and nausea. His BP is 130/80 mmHg, HR 95 bpm, SpO2 98% on room air. His 12-lead ECG shows 3 mm ST elevation in leads V1–V4 with reciprocal changes in the inferior leads. The nearest primary PCI-capable centre is 25 minutes away. What is the most appropriate immediate management?",
