    subtopic: "STEMI/NSTEMI",
    stem: "A 61-year-old woman with hypertension and hyperlipidaemia presents with a 3-hour history of central chest tightness, diaphoresis, and vomiting. Her ECG shows ST depression of 2 mm in leads V4–V6 and T-wave inversion in I and aVL. Her initial troponin I is 0.45 ng/mL (upper limit of normal 0.04 ng/mL). She has no haemodynamic instability. What is the most appropriate management strategy?",
