    subtopic: "Hypertension",
    stem: "A 52-year-old man presents to the emergency department with a severe headache, blurred vision, and confusion. His BP is 238/142 mmHg. Fundoscopy reveals bilateral papilloedema and flame haemorrhages. Urinalysis shows 2+ protein and 1+ blood. His serum creatinine is 198 µmol/L (previously normal 6 months ago). ECG shows left ventricular hypertrophy. What is the most appropriate immediate management?",
