    topic: "Cardiovascular",
    subtopic: "Valvular Disease",
    stem: "A 28-year-old woman who is 20 weeks pregnant presents with increasing dyspnoea, orthopnoea, and a new mid-diastolic murmur at the apex with an opening snap. She reports a history of rheumatic fever as a child. Echocardiography confirms mitral stenosis with a valve area of 1.0 cm² and a transmitral gradient of 14 mmHg. She has no atrial fibrillation. Her pulmonary artery pressure is estimated at 55 mmHg. What is the most appropriate management?",
