    topic: "Cardiovascular",
    subtopic: "Arrhythmias",
    stem: "A 67-year-old woman with no cardiac history is brought to the ED by ambulance after collapsing at home. She is awake and complaining of dizziness and near-syncope. Her BP is 86/52 mmHg and HR is 38 bpm. Her ECG shows P waves at a regular rate of 80 bpm with no consistent relationship to QRS complexes, which are wide (QRS 160 ms) and occurring at 38 bpm. She has no chest pain. What is the most appropriate immediate management?",
