    topic: "Cardiovascular",
    subtopic: "Cardiomyopathy",
    stem: "A 38-year-old man presents with a 3-week history of progressive dyspnoea, orthopnoea, and peripheral oedema developing after a flu-like illness 4 weeks ago. He does not drink alcohol. On examination, he has an S3 gallop, displaced apex beat, and elevated JVP. Echocardiography reveals a dilated left ventricle with global hypokinesia and EF of 22%. Cardiac MRI shows late gadolinium enhancement in a mid-myocardial, non-ischaemic pattern. Coronary angiography is normal. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
