    stem: "A 65-year-old man with a 50 pack-year smoking history attends for a routine abdominal ultrasound which incidentally reveals a fusiform infrarenal abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) measuring 4.2 cm in maximal diameter. He is asymptomatic. His BP is 148/88 mmHg and he is on no regular medications. He has no family history of AAA. What is the most appropriate management?",
